FBIS4-45201 "jptdd023__l94045" JPRS-TDD-94-023-L JPRS Narcotics 7 May 1994 LATIN AMERICA MEXICO Over One Ton of Marijuana Seized From Truck in Michoacan Over One Ton of Marijuana Seized From Truck in Michoacan 94WB0039F Mexico City EXCELSIOR in Spanish 7 May 94 p 1-A-3 94WB0039F Mexico City EXCELSIOR Spanish CSO [Text] Morelia, Michoacan, 6 May--The Attorney General's Office [PGR] revealed today that Federal Judicial Police agents captured an individual with over a ton of marijuana in his possession, on the Los Reyes-Zamora highway. The subject in custody is Enrique Calderon Duran, aged 45, a native of Apatzingan, employed as a taxi driver. He claimed to have received 500 new pesos for transporting the grass to Los Reyes. The driver was carrying 144 packages of the drug, with a total weight of 1,012 kg, on a pickup truck, concealed under cattle hides intended for tanning. He said that he was supposed to deliver the merchandise to someone in Tierra Caliente. The presumed drug trafficker was captured during a routine inspection on the aforementioned road, near the municipality of Jacona. The agents who discovered the drugs immediately arrested the subject, confiscating the packages and the pickup truck. The PGR in Michoacan reported that the drugs and the subject in custody were left at the disposal of the Federal Public Prosecutor's Office, so that the pertinent interrogations could be conducted.
